a) receiving an application from an individual or business seeking the community tax certificate or permit;

b) verifying the identity of the applicant using verifiable credentials;

c) issuing a digital certificate containing relevant information about the community tax certificate or permit to the applicant's digital wallet on a blockchain;

d) storing the digital certificate on the blockchain;

e) providing a payment provision using digital wallets on the blockchain;

f) verifying the payment using machine learning algorithms; and

g) delivering the digital certificate to the applicant's digital wallet on the blockchain.

